$interpreted: Pang: Master Yan Bo, what if the assassins come back here?
Yan Bo: Worry not. Deal with them, I will...
Hestia: Or you can come with us, Yan Bo.
Yan Bo: But If I go... Maple Lake's platypuses will be eaten up, I worry...
Hestia: Too bad, I really want you to come~
Yan Bo: Well, join you I cannot—but gift, I can give~
Pang: Master Yan Bo, this is...?
Yan Bo: Ohoh—secret, secret! Just know, Alliance's arbiter is an old friend of mine.
Pang: The current arbiter?
Yan Bo: Come to an impasse, seek her out. Assist you, she will.
Pang: I understand. Thank you, master.
Puggi: Oh the eastern beauties~ Three-thousand strong~
Puggi: Let's go! I want to see all the hot eastern babes, like the ones in Yan Bo's poems!

Yan Bo: Oho! And see them you shall, little master! 
Now, hurry forth and hurry back. Be safe.
Pang: You too, Master.
Hestia: Take care~! I'll bring back lots of snacks for ya!

Yan Bo: Will you go on, I pray? This is the night~
That ever I was born to set it right...
Pang: (Seems like the Desert Kingdom is getting busier. I wonder how Jia Shen is doing?)
Pang: (Too bad we don't have time to visit him.)
Hestia: Pang~ We found where to buy boat tickets~
Puggi: Hey, P-Boy, I think I see some guys selling tickets over there, too. I'm gonna go check it out!
Pang: No wasting time.
Hestia: Wow, I've never seen so many lizards before~
Puggi: Bummer there's no time to take you around my old stomping grounds—the one and only Oasis Casino!
Merry Merchant: Good thing that huge storm didn't hit the harbor! Then we'd have no way to get our wares in here!
Worried Merchant: At least the Desert Kingdom and Holy Shrine worked together for once...
Worried Merchant: So we could all rest easy....
Merry Merchant: Don't worry, I know the trade routes are still a little barren right now, but the kingdom will be back to its glory days before long!
Hestia: Excuse me~ Do not many boats go east, or something?
Merry Merchant: Oh wow! A mermaid! Are you a tourist?
Hestia: Sort of! We're looking to go to the East Alliance.
Hestia: But I never thought so many people would be getting tickets...
Merry Merchant: The seas are full of pirates now, so commuter ships are few and far between.
Worried Merchant: In fact, before the Kingdom of the Sun sent some of their navy to protect our waters, there weren't any commuter boats at all.
Pang: Is that so...
Worried Merchant: Thinking about it, Queen Angelia hasn't shown her face in quite a while. I wonder if everything's alright?
Merry Merchant: It's fine! I'm sure both kingdoms are just figuring out some new trade agreements or something. They'll fill us in afterward!
Crazy Thug: Make way, make way!
Hestia: Hey! No cutting in line!
Raving Thug: Well on account o' this being our territory, we can cut the line any time we damn well please!
Crazy Thug: Oi, you there! Twenty tickets!
Merry Merchant: Twenty tickets!? But that's every seat! It's enough that there are already so few ships, but now...
Merry Merchant: You just know they'll re-sell them at some ridiculous price, too! The nerve!
Pang: Unforgivable.
Puggi: Hey buddy! We've been lining up for ages! What gives you the right!?
Puggi: That's it—You wanna cut!? I'll give you a cut!!
Crazy Thug: You're all mental! W-We just wanted a vacation, is all!
Puggi: And Puggi, the great hero, once again brings peace to the Desert Kingdom!
Puggi: Please, please, it's nothing! All in a day's work!
Boat Ticket Man: Here you are, three tickets! Enjoy your trip!
Pang: Thank you.
